==English==
===Etymology===
Probably derived from obs. Sc. word ''hink'', from OE. ''inca'', doubt. Possibly from ''hank,''a loop or coil or, fig., anything that curbs or restrains
===Adjective===
'''hinky'''
# Suspicious, strange, unusual; acting in a manner as if having something to hide, or seemingly crooked.
